    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="543"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2077</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Counselor of the British Embassy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chilton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1921</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Chilton</hi>: I have received the letter (370)
                    of the 14th instant in which you advise me of the views of the British
                    Government with respect to the proposals for the reorganization of the system of
                    international control of the Chinese Eastern Railway. It is a matter of genuine
                    regret to me that the view taken by the British Government seems to disappoint
                    the hopes of cooperation, in this important phase of the situation in the Far
                    East, which this Government had founded upon the discussions on this subject
                    which have taken place during the past year.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E. Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
